Explanation:

We use a depth-first search (DFS) algorithm to solve the problem. We iterate through all courses and mark them as visited. If we find a course that can be visited from the starting course (b), we return true. Otherwise, we mark the starting course (b) as visited and return false.

The time complexity is O(n) because we visit each course exactly once. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a vector to store the visited courses.

